citations:
    citation-agot-daenerys-viii:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Daenerys VIII"
            text_from_source: "I am named Mirri Maz Duur. I am godswife of this temple … 'Make them stop,' she commanded Ser Jorah. … 'You are your brother's sister, in truth.' 'Viserys?' … 'No,' he answered. 'Rhaegar.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Khal Drogo's khalasar attacks and defeats Khal Ogo's khalasar and a Lhazareen (Lamb Men) town. Ogo and his son Fogo are both slain by Drogo. Drogo is wounded: an arrow through the arm and a deep arakh cut on his chest (losing his left nipple). Daenerys intervenes to stop rapes of Lhazareen women, claiming them as slaves for their protection. Mago (of Ko Jhaqo's khas) confronts Drogo over Daenerys's claim of his 'spoils.' Drogo sides with Daenerys. Mirri Maz Duur, a Lhazareen godswife and healer, is introduced. She trained in Asshai, with a moonsinger of the Jogos Nhai, and with a maester (Marwyn from the Citadel) who taught her the Common Tongue. Mirri treats Drogo's wounds with plasters and ointments, stitching his chest. Dany asks Mirri to attend her birth. Qotho warns Mirri that if Drogo suffers, she will too. Khal Ogo's bloodriders' bells cut and added to Drogo's braid."
